AB  - This paper presents simple conditions and a simple proof of the existence of equilibrium in asset markets where short-selling is allowed and satiation is possible. Unlike standard non-satiation assumptions, the one used here is weak enough to be reasonable in the mean-variance Capital Asset Pricing Model and in asset market models where investors maximize expected utility and where total returns to individual assets may be negative.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
